==Trivia==
*In the comics, Darren Cross was a technology industrialist. His heart was failing, so he murdered homeless people and took their hearts to keep himself alive. [[Scott Lang]] fought Cross when he kidnapped [[w:c:marvel:Erica Sondheim|Erica Sondheim]], the only person who could cure [[Cassie Lang]]. When Lang and Cross fought, Cross died of a massive coronary.
**Yellowjacket is one of the many heroic identities taken by [[Hank Pym]] in the comics. During his first time donning the [[Yellowjacket Suit|Yellowjacket suit]], Hank Pym's mental state greatly suffered due to the Pym particles affecting his brain chemistry.
**In response to his introduction in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], he was resurrected and eventually took up the mantle of Yellowjacket.
*In the comics, '''George Tarleton''' was a technician working for [[A.I.M.]] who was mutated into the highly intelligent '''M.O.D.O.C.''' (Mental Organism Designed Only for Computing), but his transformation turned him mad, and he subsequently changed his name to '''M.O.D.O.K.''' (Mental Organism Designed Only for Killing). Tartleton was also a member of the super-villain group known as [[Intelligencia]] which is composed of the smartest villains in the Marvel Universe.
*The ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' episode ''[[The Return]]'' contains a subtle allusion to M.O.D.O.K. when [[Anton Ivanov]] states that his [[Life-Model Decoy]] is "designed only for killing".
*Cross listens to [[The Cure]].

==Behind the Scenes==
*According to ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania]]'' writer [[Jeff Loveness]], his version of M.O.D.O.K. was inspired by Otto West ({{WPS|Kevin Klin}}) from ''{{WPS|A Fish Called Wanda}}'' and Frank Grimes ({{WPS|Hank Azaria}}) from ''{{WPS|The Simpsons}}'', describing him as ''"really put-upon, selfish, entitled but then also deeply sad, insecure man who knows that he got a shit deal in life and is trying to make the best of it"''.<ref>[https://www.gamesradar.com/ant-man-and-the-wasp-quantumania-modok-inspiration/ Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania writer breaks down MODOK inspiration: "He’s a real loose cannon"]</ref>
*''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' co-writer [[Christopher Markus]] had considered featuring M.O.D.O.K. as the main villain in the film, with [[Peter Dinklage]] being named as his choice to portray the character.<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/news/2599259/captain-america-writer-wants-peter-dinklage-as-modok-for-sequel/ 'Captain America' Writer Wants Peter Dinklage As MODOK For Sequel]</ref>
*Concept art for the film ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]'' depicted M.O.D.O.K. in the crowd while [[Captain Marvel]] participates in battles.
*''[[New Warriors (TV series)|New Warriors]]'' showrunner [[Kevin Biegel]] had a "seasons-long plan" to turn [[Keith David]]'s character [[Ernest Vigman]] into a version of M.O.D.O.K. However, the show was shelved before it got to air.<ref>[https://screenrant.com/marvel-new-warriors-show-modok-debut-keith-david/ Canceled New Warriors Show Would Have Been M.O.D.O.K. Live-Action Debut]</ref>
*''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' showrunners originally planned to introduce M.O.D.O.K. in the series' [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D./Season Seven|final season]], but the idea was shut down by [[Marvel Studios]] despite the showrunners having initially been given permission.<ref>[https://www.avclub.com/the-agents-of-s-h-i-e-l-d-showrunners-reveal-the-plan-1844694196 The ''Agents Of S.H.I.E.L.D.'' showrunners reveal the plan behind that grand series finale]</ref>
*[[Kevin Cassidy]] was a stunt double for [[Corey Stoll]] in the role of Yellowjacket.

